.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-04-PLAN.md:27:**Task 2 — `writeVarByName` for SwgVertexConstants `material[N]` array schema.** Plan 17-03's R3-03g flush log confirmed `wroteDiffuse / wroteSpecular / wroteEmissive = 0 / 0 / 0` for all char-select shaders despite valid source data. The reflected cbuffer at b0 is `SwgVertexConstants` (the VS-side cbuffer reused by the recompiled HLSL PS programs because they `#include` the VS rewrite header) and exposes constants as `material[N]` array elements (per `vertex_shader_constants.inc`), NOT as the `materialDiffuse / materialSpecular / materialEmissive` names Plan 17-03's executor coded. Update `writeVarByName` (or the surrounding apply()-loop logic) to discover the actual variable names from the reflected layout and write source values into the correct array slots. Source data (`pm.m_diffuse / pm.m_specular / pm.m_emissive`) is already correctly resolved at construct() time per SR-1 — only the upload-side name lookup needs to be schema-aware.
.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-04-PLAN.md:40:- **Plan 17-03** (merged `34a988ca3` + `45f5c895a` close-out) — `Direct3d11_StaticShaderData::construct` caches per-pass material source data (`PerPassMaterial` with diffuse/specular/emissive/textureFactor/power, all properly resolved from `shader.getMaterial`/`getTextureFactor`). `apply()` iterates reflected cbuffer layouts and uploads via `Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer::updatePS(layout.BindPoint, staging, layout.TotalSize)`. R3-03g flush proof log shows `wroteDiffuse=0 wroteSpecular=0 wroteEmissive=0` across sul_eye + sul_m_head (and by extension all 4407 apply() invocations) because `writeVarByName("materialDiffuse"/...)` doesn't match SwgVertexConstants's actual variable names. Defensive 64 KiB cap on `layout.TotalSize` in place (belt-and-braces; trace evidence showed all TotalSizes are 400 B).
.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-04-PLAN.md:104:**The schema problem.** Plan 17-03 hardcoded names: `materialDiffuse`, `materialSpecular`, `materialEmissive`, `textureFactor`, `textureFactor2`. These don't exist in `SwgVertexConstants`. The reflected cbuffer has 9 variables (per D3DReflect dump at `PS-cbuffer: ... totalSize=400 vars=9`). The actual names are likely (per `vertex_shader_constants.inc` referenced in Plan 17-03's executor note): `objectWorldCameraProjectionMatrix`, `material[N]` array (5 elements), `lightData[N]` array, etc.
.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-04-PLAN.md:117:**Update writeVarByName lookups** to use the discovered names. Keep the current hardcoded-name lookups too — if a future shader DOES declare `materialDiffuse` (e.g., a PS that doesn't `#include` the VS header), the writes still land. Multiple candidate names per source value:
