.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-03-SUMMARY.md:328:### 2. [Out-of-scope observation — caveat for Phase 17.X / 18] Reflected cbuffer variable names likely don't match the `materialDiffuse` candidate set
.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-03-SUMMARY.md:331:- **Observation:** Char-select PS programs all reflect the rewriter-emitted `SwgVertexConstants` cbuffer at b0 (the VS-style include cbuffer). Its variables are whatever `vertex_shader_constants.inc` declares (typically `material[5]` array layout, not 5 named scalars `materialDiffuse / materialSpecular / materialEmissive`). The writeVarByName lambda will silently miss all 5 names, and the staging buffer's `material*` fields stay at offset 0 zero-fill — which means the upload writes 400 bytes of mostly-zero into the cbuffer slot the VS is also reading, **potentially zeroing the WVP matrix and the lightData**.
