.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-03-CLOSEOUT.md:92:- **Task #7** (writeVarByName for SwgVertexConstants schema): confirmed via R3-03g — `wrote*` flags all zero despite valid source-data. The variable names Plan 17-03's executor used (`materialDiffuse/Specular/Emissive`) don't exist in SwgVertexConstants. Need to either extend `writeVarByName` to recognize `material[N]` array elements, OR add a separate PerMaterial cbuffer that the recompiled PS targets.
.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-03-PLAN.md:24:    - "Per Round 3 R3-03b (HIGH-3 stale-shadow fix — Cursor HIGH): the per-pass apply() always uploads a current material set, even when `!pm.m_materialValid` for a pass. Either (a) the apply() zeros materialDiffuse/Specular/Emissive (and textureFactor fields if extended) in the staging buffer before flushing `updatePS(layout.BindPoint, staging.data(), layout.TotalSize)` for non-material passes, OR (b) it uploads the full per-pass struct EVERY pass mirroring D3D9 `Pass::apply` semantics (Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:835-897) via the same `updatePS(layout.BindPoint, ...)` call. Round 2's `if (wroteAny) updatePS(...)` was the bug — a non-material pass between two material passes leaves the GPU reading the prior draw's values. CHAR-02/03 fail silently when body→head→eye passes inherit material from each other; this fix closes that."
.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-03-PLAN.md:25:    - "Per Round 3 R3-03c (SR-2 reflection-driven upload — CONVERGENT HIGH, both reviewers): Plan 03's per-pass material upload writes through reflected variable OFFSETS into a staging byte buffer sized to the cbuffer's reflected TotalSize, and uploads via `Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer::updatePS(layout.BindPoint, staging, layout.TotalSize)`. **Contract A (generic, preferred per D-04 \"generic reflect\")**: for each named variable (materialDiffuse / materialSpecular / materialEmissive / textureFactor / textureFactor2) present in the reflected layout, write XMFLOAT4 source data at `var.StartOffset` (bounds-checked against `var.Size`). The cbuffer slot bound to the shader is `layout.BindPoint`, NOT a hardcoded `2`. (Contract B narrow-gate is documented as an alternative — see <objective> — but the plan implements Contract A so it survives a $Globals or non-b2 PSRC.)"
.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-03-PLAN.md:30:    - "Per Round 3 R3-03g (shadow flush-time log proof for HIGH-3 + R3-03b): a one-shot DEBUG_REPORT_LOG_PRINT (or InfoQueue dual-route) inside Direct3d11_StaticShaderData::apply() at the flush point logs the shadow's materialDiffuse + materialSpecular + materialEmissive + (textureFactor if extended) AT the next updatePS(2,...) call for the HEAD pass and the EYE pass (two consecutive multi-pass apply() invocations). The expected result is that consecutive passes with DIFFERENT material data produce DIFFERENT logged values — proving R3-03b's contract that non-material passes do not leave stale data on the GPU."
.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-03-PLAN.md:68:      via: "one-shot log of shadow.materialDiffuse/Specular/Emissive at HEAD and EYE pass flushes; proves consecutive-pass divergence (R3-03b)"
.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-03-PLAN.md:86:- **R3-03b (Cursor HIGH):** Per-pass apply() ALWAYS uploads a current material set. When `!pm.m_materialValid` for a pass, the shadow's `materialDiffuse/Specular/Emissive` (and `textureFactor` fields if extended) are ZEROED before `updatePS(layout.BindPoint, staging, layout.TotalSize)`. Round 2's `if (wroteAny) updatePS(...)` was the bug — multi-pass char-select (body → head → eye) silently inherits prior pass's material.
.planning\phases\17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead\17-03-PLAN.md:91:- **R3-03g (Cursor HIGH proof, R3-03b implementation evidence):** A one-shot DEBUG_REPORT_LOG_PRINT (dual-routed via InfoQueue per the Plan 02 R3-02b precedent) inside `Direct3d11_StaticShaderData::apply()` at the flush point logs the shadow's `materialDiffuse + Specular + Emissive` AT the next `updatePS(...)` call for the HEAD pass AND the EYE pass — proving consecutive passes with different material data produce different cbuffer contents. Without this proof, R3-03b's contract is unfalsifiable.
