VERDICT: CASE-C-CORRECT

(a) I found no Case-B citation. Rule D only wraps global `: register(cN)` declarations into `cbuffer SwgVertexConstants : register(b0)` and substitutes `register` with `packoffset`, preserving the original `cN` text: [Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp:747), [Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp:973). It does not contain a `materialDiffuse/materialEmissive -> userConstants[N]` or `packedRegisterN` table.

(b) I found no other deterministic engine-side source. `setPixelShaderUserConstants_impl` copies `constants[i]` into `shadow.userConstants[i]` positionally: [Direct3d11.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11.cpp:679), [Direct3d11.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11.cpp:702). The D3D9 side proves material is separate from user constants: `VSCR_material = 11`, `VCSR_userConstant0 = 52`: [Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h:27), [Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h:37). D3D9 material upload uses `VSCR_material`, not user constants: [Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:862).

(c) Your Case C reasoning is sound. The repo even documents the live reflected shape as generic `packedRegister0..4`, named `textureFactor`, `textureFactor2`, `materialSpecularColor`, and opaque `userConstants`, with `pixel_shader_constants.inc` carrying semantics outside deterministic engine code: [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:908), [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:916). The folklore-guessing prohibition is correctly applied; a guessed offset would create a false positive metric.
